description:
&lt;p&gt;CHoC are recruiting salaried GPs to work across Cumbria and are pleased to offer Tier 2 visa sponsorship for eligible candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our General Practitioners form an integral part of the CHoC team, accountable to the Chief Executive and Medical Director. As a CHoC GP you will be responsible for providing high quality primary care services to the population of Cumbria in an out of hours setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post can be part time or full time with a range of options available in terms of location, hours and working patterns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Clinicians work from sites across Cumbria (including extended access locations). Our core bases are at:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Kendal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Barrow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Whitehaven&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carlisle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Penrith&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wigton&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BENEFITS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;CHoC GPs are covered by the state-backed CNSGP scheme, and we are pleased to contribute to the additional indemnity cover of all Salaried GPs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would be delighted to further discuss the role, support networks, flexible working patterns and the other benefits available to our salaried GPs including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 weeks annual leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;study leave and ongoing training and development to meet your CPD needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;relocation packages for eligible candidates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information, please contact Juliet Eyre (Head of HR &amp; Training) on juliet.eyre@choc.nhs.uk or 01228514830&lt;/p&gt;
